{"questionId":"22499006","questionHtml":"<p>Find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>, in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>, by differentiating your answer from part (b).</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>M1A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>Award <em><strong>M1</strong></em> for use of chain rule, or use of implicit differentiation of the penultimate line of the answer to (b).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22499006","referenceCode":"24M.2.AHL.TZ1.5c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find dydx, in terms of x, by differentiating your answer from part (b).","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.9—Differentiating standard functions and derivative rules"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}